longBusinessSummary: Sedana Medical AB (publ), a medtech and pharmaceutical company, develops, manufactures, and sells medical devices and pharmaceutical products in Sweden, Germany, and internationally. The company offers Sedaconda ACD-L and Sedaconda ACD-S, which are disposable medical devices that enable the administration of volatile anaesthetics; Sedaconda Syringe, a 50/60ml syringe; Sedaconda ACD starter kit; Sedaconda (Isoflurane) for sedation of mechanically ventilated adult patients during intensive care; and AnaConDa, a medical device enabling the administration of inhaled anaesthetics. It also provides FlurAbsorb and FlurAbsorb-S, which are active carbon filters to capture waste anaesthetic gases from the exhaust of the ventilator; scavenging tube, a one-piece pre-connected tube designed to channel anaesthetic waste gas from the ventilator exhaust port and the gas monitor exhaust port to the FlurAbsorb filter; FlurAbsorb mount to hold the FlurAbsorb during scavenging of anaesthetic gas; FlurAbsorb-S mount to hold the FlurAbsorb-S during scavenging of anaesthetic gas; FlurAbsorb accessory kit comprising accessories to connect the exhaust of the ventilator and the gas monitor to FlurAbsorb/FlurAbsorb-S; and Mindray exhaust connector, which enables connection of the exhaust of the ventilator to an active or passive scavenging system. In addition, the company offers AMG-06 Gas Monitor for continuous non-invasive sidestream monitoring of CO2 and anaesthetics concentration in inspired and expired gases; Sedaconda Filling Adapter, a single-use device for safe and easy extraction of isoflurane from a Sedaconda bottle to a Sedaconda Syringe; and a single-use standard iso/sevo adapter that is designed to fit standard threaded isoflurane and sevoflurane bottles. Further, it provides DRYLINE II and WaterLock 2 water traps, Nafion dryer tubing, respiratory gas monitoring lines, and gas sampling line H products. The company was founded in 1999 and is headquartered in Danderyd, Sweden.
